#: 3470b3eb7c9d47f4b4d4e57cf2daf806
msgid ""
"Even though we do have a small DHCP server that runs inside the HVM's "
"untrusted stub domain to make the manual network configuration unnecessary "
"for many qubes, this won't work for most modern Linux distributions, which "
"contain Xen networking PV drivers (but not Qubes tools), which bypass the "
"stub-domain networking. (Their net frontends connect directly to the net "
"backend in the [netvm](/doc/glossary/#netvm).) In this instance, our DHCP "
"server is not useful."
msgstr ""

